public sealed interface TypeSet extends Set<Class<?>>
The TypeSet interface is the Set counterpart to the TypeMap interface. As with TypeMap, the TypeSet does not specify any methods of its own. It is the behavior required of implementations that take it beyond the Set interface. See the class comments for TypeMap for a detailed explanation. The behavior of the contains method must follow the same logic as the containKey method of TypeMap. In practice all implementations are backed by a TypeMap instance.
